.START 

Upjohn Co. and Rorer Group Inc. have signed an agreement that gives Upjohn the right to co-market or distribute two of Rorer's products in various parts of the world. 

Rorer, based in Fort Washington, Pa., granted certain marketing rights to Upjohn outside the U.S. for Rorer's Selectol, a drug for the treament of hypertension.
In addition, Upjohn received co-marketing rights in West Germany, France, Italy and Spain for Rorer's Frumil, a diuretic. 

In August, the pharmaceutical companies had agreed to market jointly two drugs in the U.S. 

